column5: I bowhunted hard all season long, passed up many bucks waiting for a certain non-typical 12, but finally settled on this little fella dec.19. 4.5 yard chip shot and he dropped within sight, 50 yards behind my buddy in his ground blind.  How did yall make out this deer season?         heres the two fellers i arrowed last year    and the little 10
Dude.... you need to wash your face pig-pen! (character from Peanuts)  just kidding..  Nice looking baby buck you got there!... Mmmmm... back straps n' pepperettes!  G.
My deer is not dead though....        RFS
Awesome bucks mossyoak Nice looking non typical Can't post any pics cause did not get any this season Leechman
I was skunked by Whitetails too.

I filled my buddy's tag as well and we split the meat.  Both NW Ontario bucks.  Those are some dandy's mossyoak!!  I have a lot of respect for those guys who bow hunt.  Definitely on my hunting 'to-do' list.
Love your red eyes goes good with the red hands!
